⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Father Zosima
node BKZ · BKZ · ⟦Father Zosima:BKZ:63847e⟧

WHO   — Father Zosima — the elder · active love
WHAT  — The novel's wellspring of grace: he teaches ‘active love’ and that ‘each of us is guilty before all, for all,’ and bows to Dmitri's coming suffering.
WHERE — BKZ · The Brothers Karamazov  Framework inputs: The Brothers Karamazov (Dostoevsky, 1880)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Ivan's case needed a counter-voice not of argument but of sanctity — a life that has already answered the question by living it.
HOW   — By humility, counsel, and a doctrine of universal responsibility; even his death (his body decaying ‘too soon’) tests the faithful.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Each of us is guilty before everyone, for everyone and everything — love is harsh labour, not a dream; that is the whole of my answer to your despair.

